Shishito Gazpacho

4 oz shishito peppers (1 package of ~15-18)
1 1/2 lbs ripe tomatoes, peeled, seeded, and chopped
1 c cucumber, peeled, seeded, and chopped
1 small jalapeno, seeded and minced
1 medium garlic clove, minced
1/4 c evoo
1/2 c tomato juice
juice of 1 lime
1/2 c chopped red bell pepper
1/2 c chopped red onion
2 tsp basalmic vinegar
2 tsp worcestershire sauce
1/2 tsp cumin
1 tsp salt
1/4 tsp black pepper
sliced avocado for serving
cilantro for serving
sour cream for serving

Bring a large pot of water to a boil. With a paring knife, scor the bottom of the tomatoes with an X. Drop the tomatoes and shishito peppers into the boiling water. Remove the tomatoes after 15 s, remove the shishitos after 3 min. Transfer both to an ice bath and let cool for ~1 min. Remove and pat dry. Stem and coarsly chop the shishitos and place in a large bowl. Peel, core, and seed the tomatoes, and add to the shishitos. Add tomato juice to the mixture. Add the cucumber, bell pepper, red onion, jalapeno, garlic, evoo, lime juice, basalmic, worcestershire, cumin, salt, and pepper, and stir to combine. Pour 1 1/2 c of the mixture into a blender and puree at high speed for 15 s. Return the pureed mixture to the bowl and stir to combine. Cover and chill for at least 2 hrs, up to overnight. Serve with avocado, cilantro, and sour cream.
